full_text:
You might try ExpressPCB, their minimum is two boards. I'm working on a 
layout now, it's $93 for two boards, of course you have to install the 
parts, and over half of this layout is surface mount, so I can use both 
sides of the board for different functions, and make it smaller for reduced 
cost. These first two are to make it works, and every thing's cosher.
You have to draw the layout using their cad software, then e-mail it with 
credit card #.

Frank-S
